:v: eric-wieser can now approve this pull request. To approve and merge a pull request, simply reply with `bors r+`. More detailed instructions are available [here](https://bors.tech/documentation/getting-started/#reviewing-pull-requests).
I hope we can decide soon if we can merge this PR (or the first version of it).

`Zero` has been moved to the core. I wish we could decide what should be done. I'm pretty sure this gives a more significant performance boost after adjusting the type class search path. See [run comparison](http://speed.lean-fro.org/mathlib4/compare/6c55746e-f251-4cf1-ae7d-5a103bb3424b/to/d5e5f673-49c7-4bd7-8d75-2ed3ab347c13) between https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/7873#issuecomment-2156442983 and https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/7873#issuecomment-2157272112. @eric-wieser
Do we even need this instance? This looks like a performance trap with no benefits to me.
